name: Production E2E Tests

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]
  schedule:
    - cron: '0 6 * * *'  # Daily at 6 AM UTC
  workflow_dispatch:  # Allow manual triggering

jobs:
  e2e-full-suite:
    name: Full E2E Test Suite
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    
    services:
      postgres:
        image: postgis/postgis:16-3.4
        env:
          POSTGRES_PASSWORD: postgres
          POSTGRES_DB: fowldata
        options: >-
          --health-cmd pg_isready
          --health-interval 10s
          --health-timeout 5s
          --health-retries 5
        ports:
          - 5432:5432

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      
      - name: Get current week
        id: date
        run: echo "week=$(date +'%Y-W%U')" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
        
      - name: Set up Docker Buildx
        uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3
        
      - name: Build backend with cache
        uses: docker/build-push-action@v5
        with:
          context: .
          file: ./Dockerfile
          cache-from: |
            type=gha,scope=backend-cache-prod
            type=gha,scope=backend-cache
          cache-to: type=gha,mode=max,scope=backend-cache-prod
          tags: fowldata-backend:prod
          build-args: |
            DEV=true
          load: true
          
      - name: Build frontend with cache
        uses: docker/build-push-action@v5
        with:
          context: ./frontend
          file: ./frontend/Dockerfile.ci
          cache-from: |
            type=gha,scope=frontend-cache-prod
            type=gha,scope=frontend-cache
          cache-to: type=gha,mode=max,scope=frontend-cache-prod
          tags: fowldata-frontend:prod
          load: true
      
      - name: Setup environment files for production E2E
        run: |
          cp .env.ci .env.local
          cp frontend/.env.ci frontend/.env.local
          
      - name: Start services
        env:
          AUTH_SECRET: production-e2e-secret-not-for-real-use
          GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID: test-google-client-id
          GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET: test-google-client-secret
          NEXTAUTH_URL: http://localhost:3000
        run: |
          docker compose -f docker-compose.ci.yaml up -d
          
      - name: Wait for services
        run: |
          echo "Waiting for services to be ready..."
          for i in {1..30}; do
            if curl -f http://localhost:8000/admin/ 2>/dev/null && \
               curl -f http://localhost:3000/ 2>/dev/null; then
              echo "Services ready!"
              break
            fi
            echo "Waiting for services... ($i/30)"
            sleep 10
          done
          
      - name: Run complete E2E test suite
        run: |
          cd frontend
          # Run all E2E tests with retries for production reliability
          npm run test:e2e || npm run test:e2e  # Retry once on failure
        
      - name: Upload E2E test artifacts
        if: failure()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: e2e-test-results
          path: |
            frontend/test-results/
            frontend/playwright-report/
          retention-days: 7
        
      - name: Cleanup
        if: always()
        run: docker compose -f docker-compose.ci.yaml down -v

services:
  fowldata:  # Django backend container
      build:
        context: .
        args:
          - DEV="true"
      # No ports needed with host networking
      volumes:
        - ./fowldata:/fowldata
      user: "root"  # Use root in CI for volume mount permissions
      command: >
        sh -c "echo 'Starting Django backend with environment validation...' &&
               echo 'Checking working directory permissions...' &&
               ls -la /fowldata/ || echo 'Permission issue with /fowldata - trying alternate approach' &&
               echo 'Current user and groups:' &&
               id &&
               echo 'Attempting to access manage.py...' &&
               ls -la /fowldata/manage.py || echo 'Cannot access manage.py' &&
               echo 'Environment Variables:' &&
               echo 'DB_USER:' $$DB_USER &&
               echo 'DB_HOST:' $$DB_HOST &&
               echo 'BACKEND_URL:' $$BACKEND_URL &&
               echo 'SECRET_KEY:' $$(echo $$SECRET_KEY | head -c 10)... &&
               echo 'Current user:' $$(whoami) &&
               echo 'Waiting for database...' &&
               echo 'Testing database connection with current user context...' &&
               echo 'Attempting manual database connection test...' &&
               python -c \"import os,psycopg2; conn=psycopg2.connect(host=os.environ.get('DB_HOST','localhost'),database=os.environ.get('DB_NAME','fowldata'),user=os.environ.get('DB_USER','postgres'),password=os.environ.get('DB_PASS','postgres'),port=os.environ.get('DB_PORT','5432')); print('✓ Direct PostgreSQL connection successful!'); conn.close()\" ||
               (echo '✗ Direct PostgreSQL connection failed' && exit 1) &&
               echo 'Verifying Django database configuration...' &&
               python manage.py shell -c \"from django.conf import settings; print('Django DB_USER:', settings.DATABASES['default']['USER']); print('Django DB_HOST:', settings.DATABASES['default']['HOST']); print('Django DB_NAME:', settings.DATABASES['default']['NAME']); print('Django DB_PORT:', settings.DATABASES['default']['PORT'])\" &&
               echo 'Using Django wait_for_db command...' &&
               python manage.py wait_for_db &&
               echo 'Database connection successful! Running migrations...' &&
               python manage.py migrate --noinput &&
               echo 'Creating test user...' &&
               python manage.py create_test_user --force &&
               echo 'Test user creation completed' &&
               echo 'Validating test user exists...' &&
               python manage.py shell -c \"from django.contrib.auth import get_user_model; User = get_user_model(); print('Test user exists:', User.objects.filter(email='mark@mail.com').exists())\" &&
               echo 'Starting Django server...' &&
               python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000"
      environment:
        SECRET_KEY: ${SECRET_KEY:-github-actions-secret-key}
        DEBUG: "True"
        DB_HOST: ${DB_HOST:-localhost}
        DB_NAME: ${DB_NAME:-fowldata}
        DB_USER: postgres  # Force PostgreSQL user (not system user)
        DB_PASS: postgres  # GitHub Actions PostgreSQL service default
        DB_PORT: "5432"
        ALLOWED_HOSTS: localhost,127.0.0.1
        CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS: http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000
        # Backend URL for internal communication - use env var if available
        BACKEND_URL: ${BACKEND_URL:-http://localhost:8000}
        # Weather API and other services
        WEATHERAPI_KEY: ${WEATHERAPI_KEY:-e1d03b3683514ec582d233553250608}
        USE_S3: "False"
        # Ensure UTF-8 encoding
        PYTHONIOENCODING: utf-8
        LANG: C.UTF-8
      network_mode: "host"
      # No dependencies since PostgreSQL runs as GitHub Actions service
      healthcheck:
        test: ["CMD-SHELL", "curl -f http://localhost:8000/admin/ || exit 1"]
        interval: 10s
        timeout: 5s
        retries: 5
        start_period: 30s

  frontend:  # Next.js frontend container
    build:
      context: ./frontend
      dockerfile: Dockerfile.ci
    # No ports needed with host networking
    environment:
      # API Configuration - use env vars with fallbacks
      - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=${BACKEND_URL:-http://localhost:8000}/api
      - BACKEND_URL=${BACKEND_URL:-http://localhost:8000}
      # Environment flag for CI detection
      - NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV=${NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV:-ci}
      # NextAuth Configuration
      - NEXTAUTH_URL=${NEXTAUTH_URL:-http://localhost:3000}
      - AUTH_URL=${NEXTAUTH_URL:-http://localhost:3000}
      - AUTH_SECRET=${AUTH_SECRET:-fallback-secret-for-ci}
      # OAuth Configuration (CI test values)
      - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=${GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID:-test-client-id}
      - GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=${GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET:-test-client-secret}
      # Mapbox Configuration
      - NEXT_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=pk.eyJ1IjoibWFya2VsbW9yZSIsImEiOiJjbHg5cTE4aDQycW1vMnFxNmFmdHMwaWpjIn0.6_cVzc0hKksNdvQ_unYS_w
      # Node environment
      - NODE_ENV=${NODE_ENV:-development}
    depends_on:
      fowldata:
        condition: service_healthy
    network_mode: "host"
    restart: "on-failure"
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "curl -f http://localhost:3000/ || exit 1"]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 5
      start_period: 30s
    command: >
      sh -c "echo 'Starting Next.js frontend with environment validation...' &&
             echo 'Environment Variables:' &&
             echo 'NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV:' $$NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV &&
             echo 'BACKEND_URL:' $$BACKEND_URL &&
             echo 'NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL:' $$NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL &&
             echo 'NEXTAUTH_URL:' $$NEXTAUTH_URL &&
             echo 'AUTH_SECRET:' $$(echo $$AUTH_SECRET | head -c 10)... &&
             echo 'NODE_ENV:' $$NODE_ENV &&
             echo 'Waiting for backend health check...' &&
             until curl -f http://localhost:8000/admin/ 2>/dev/null; do echo 'Waiting for backend...'; sleep 2; done &&
             echo 'Backend is ready, starting frontend...' &&
             npm start"
